But it's from Su Bin. It's her number.

00:47:53.159 --> 00:47:56.229
(68-Year-Old Dress from 1957 Discovered)

00:47:56.459 --> 00:47:58.769
Grandma, what do you think? Do you feel 20 again?

00:48:00.129 --> 00:48:01.939
It feels like just yesterday.

00:48:02.339 --> 00:48:05.569
- Here, let me see. What is this? - Wearing this dress,

00:48:05.909 --> 00:48:09.539
- I'd sneak out in Mom's heels. - My gosh. This is you, Ok Rye.

00:48:09.609 --> 00:48:12.579
- Everyone, come look at this. - Look at me sashaying around.

00:48:12.649 --> 00:48:15.049
- It's Ms. Ok Rye! - That's right.

00:48:15.119 --> 00:48:18.219
- You look like a model. - Wow. You look fantastic.

00:48:18.289 --> 00:48:20.989
- You look amazing. - You think so?

00:48:22.689 --> 00:48:23.759
Yes, Secretary Kang.

00:48:26.459 --> 00:48:27.459
What did you just say?

00:48:28.899 --> 00:48:30.859
He appointed Seong Jae as Vice President?

00:48:31.259 --> 00:48:34.399
Yes. The chairman gave the order suddenly today.

00:48:36.039 --> 00:48:37.039
Okay, I have to go.

00:48:40.169 --> 00:48:41.169
Park Jin Seok.

00:48:42.109 --> 00:48:43.979
What in the world are you thinking?

00:48:48.749 --> 00:48:50.519
(Ending Note: Title for the next chapter)

00:48:51.749 --> 00:48:52.889
Oh, man...

00:48:53.989 --> 00:48:55.359
I almost had it.

00:48:58.489 --> 00:48:59.659
Hey, how's it coming along?

00:48:59.929 --> 00:49:00.929
Not well!

00:49:01.599 --> 00:49:04.599
Hold on, why am I the one helping you with your webtoon plot?

00:49:05.129 --> 00:49:07.529
Tell me. Are you going to be a webtoon artist?

00:49:07.599 --> 00:49:08.899
Or are you going to marry into the Jinhwa Group?

00:49:11.169 --> 00:49:13.669
Why are you so concerned with my life?

00:49:14.739 --> 00:49:18.139
You're weird. You've been so casual since we met.

00:49:18.909 --> 00:49:21.949
Weren't you intimidated by me when we first met?

00:49:22.579 --> 00:49:23.679
What's so intimidating about you?

00:49:24.349 --> 00:49:27.149
Other drivers, people at the gym, even at the spa,

00:49:27.149 --> 00:49:28.459
everyone's intimidated by me...

00:49:29.289 --> 00:49:32.929
because my dad's a chairman, and my mom runs a foundation.

00:49:33.629 --> 00:49:35.659
Your parents are the ones with those titles.

00:49:36.799 --> 00:49:38.129
You're nothing on your own.

00:49:39.369 --> 00:49:40.369
What did you just say?

00:49:40.699 --> 00:49:42.669
You even had a ghost painter.

00:49:43.239 --> 00:49:44.699
You have nothing that's actually yours.

00:49:45.539 --> 00:49:49.709
Wait, you have your webtoon. But you can't even publish it.

00:49:49.839 --> 00:49:51.339
So, you're a nobody.

00:49:53.609 --> 00:49:55.679
How can you say something so cruel?

00:49:56.219 --> 00:50:00.119
Hey, don't cry. I can't stand it when girls cry.

00:50:00.189 --> 00:50:02.819
If you were Su Bin, I would've smacked you by now.

00:50:04.489 --> 00:50:07.129
Fine. I have nothing.

00:50:07.859 --> 00:50:10.359
That's why I'm going to marry a guy from an even better family.

00:50:10.859 --> 00:50:15.169
Hey, I never said you had nothing. I said you had your webtoon.

00:50:15.269 --> 00:50:17.499
You're the only one who likes it. Just you.

00:50:17.569 --> 00:50:19.839
I'm the only one who likes it? No way!

00:50:24.949 --> 00:50:26.779
Hey, look at this.

00:50:27.079 --> 00:50:29.419
- Your webtoon. - My webtoon?

00:50:31.049 --> 00:50:35.219
- What is this? - See what you're capable of.

00:50:35.859 --> 00:50:38.059
I posted your webtoon on Neiro.

00:50:38.559 --> 00:50:40.729
How could you upload this without telling me?

00:50:40.989 --> 00:50:45.429
Just look, and if you still hate it, I'll take it down when I get back.

00:50:58.679 --> 00:51:01.209
(Yoon Tae Sik Vice President, AP Group)

00:51:03.779 --> 00:51:04.779
Yes, hello.

00:51:05.419 --> 00:51:07.149
We met at the last HQ meeting.

00:51:07.149 --> 00:51:08.459
I'm Lee Ji Hyuk, CEO of Mamdaerozip.

00:51:08.819 --> 00:51:10.719
I'm here to see the chairman.

00:51:10.959 --> 00:51:15.099
The chairman isn't seeing anyone about the acquisition.

00:51:15.199 --> 00:51:18.829
Please tell him Lee Ji Hyuk is here. I did the Edel Orphanage renovation.

00:51:19.269 --> 00:51:20.299
Please.

00:51:23.199 --> 00:51:26.269
He worked on the Edel Orphanage renovation?

00:51:26.669 --> 00:51:27.969
He doesn't have the funds.

00:51:28.269 --> 00:51:30.279
He must be dredging up old connections.

00:51:30.839 --> 00:51:33.309
His company has nowhere near enough capital for the acquisition.

00:51:33.379 --> 00:51:36.779
But how did he know to dig up such an old connection?

00:51:53.799 --> 00:51:58.199
Why are you just staring at me without saying anything?

00:52:02.039 --> 00:52:05.379
Why do I still miss you even when you're right here?

00:52:08.009 --> 00:52:10.379
I guess I just can't get enough of looking at you.

00:52:13.949 --> 00:52:16.189
You'd only known me as an interior designer,

00:52:16.619 --> 00:52:18.459
so I imagine this is hard for you to accept.

00:52:19.489 --> 00:52:20.529
For me, too.

00:52:21.529 --> 00:52:23.529
I still just see you as the director.

00:52:28.099 --> 00:52:29.339
Not for me.

00:52:31.299 --> 00:52:35.209
So you still just see me as the director.

00:52:37.479 --> 00:52:40.479
It just doesn't feel real yet.

00:52:43.949 --> 00:52:44.949
Of course.

00:52:45.789 --> 00:52:47.689
We only just found out yesterday, after all.

00:52:50.619 --> 00:52:52.559
I suppose it's different for a mother and her child.

00:52:53.829 --> 00:52:54.889
For me,

00:52:56.429 --> 00:52:59.429
you already feel so much like my daughter.

00:53:01.599 --> 00:53:02.699
I'm sorry.

00:53:10.879 --> 00:53:12.149
Could you call me Mom...

00:53:13.949 --> 00:53:16.649
just once?

00:53:24.689 --> 00:53:26.589
I'll have to think about that.

00:53:29.529 --> 00:53:30.599
To be honest...

00:53:31.459 --> 00:53:36.269
I thought my birth parents had lost me and were in agony,

00:53:36.339 --> 00:53:38.069
so I went ahead with the DNA Registration.

00:53:38.509 --> 00:53:41.779
I never actually thought I would find you.

00:53:43.509 --> 00:53:44.539
So...

00:53:45.349 --> 00:53:47.879
I never thought about what to do...

00:53:48.819 --> 00:53:50.749
after we actually met.

00:53:52.649 --> 00:53:55.659
My gosh, I see.

00:53:56.819 --> 00:54:00.359
I'm so sorry. I didn't consider your feelings.

00:54:01.799 --> 00:54:05.369
You need time, of course. I'm sorry.

00:54:06.729 --> 00:54:07.829
No, it's okay.

00:54:17.609 --> 00:54:18.809
You said she truly...

00:54:19.449 --> 00:54:22.449
raised you with so much love.

00:54:24.349 --> 00:54:27.989
I'd like to thank your mother first, before anything else.

00:54:28.389 --> 00:54:30.919
- It's the right thing to do. - No, you can't do that.

00:54:32.829 --> 00:54:34.029
Gosh, I'm sorry.

00:54:34.529 --> 00:54:36.129
That was thoughtless of me.

00:54:37.599 --> 00:54:40.429
You haven't told your mother yet, have you?

00:54:41.969 --> 00:54:44.499
No. Not yet.

00:54:48.169 --> 00:54:49.179
But...

00:54:50.379 --> 00:54:54.149
you mentioned that my birth father died in a hit-and-run.

00:54:56.949 --> 00:54:58.719
What was he like?

00:55:04.589 --> 00:55:05.859
We really do have...

00:55:07.229 --> 00:55:09.299
so much to catch up on...

00:55:10.029 --> 00:55:11.699
for all the years we've lost.

00:55:14.199 --> 00:55:16.769
Losing my daughter tore my heart to pieces,

00:55:19.509 --> 00:55:22.479
and now my son's suffering is ripping me apart.

00:55:25.949 --> 00:55:28.779
You also mentioned that your son was sick.

00:55:30.079 --> 00:55:31.719
What's wrong with him?

00:55:33.089 --> 00:55:35.419
Did I say that my Jin was sick?

00:55:36.859 --> 00:55:39.489
Yes. You just said he was sick...

00:55:41.729 --> 00:55:42.829
I see.

00:55:47.969 --> 00:55:49.639
His liver has been in very bad shape.

00:55:51.739 --> 00:55:54.109
He needed a liver transplant,

00:55:55.979 --> 00:55:58.679
but thankfully, we found a donor and scheduled the surgery.

00:56:03.579 --> 00:56:05.489
So it's really serious, then.

00:56:10.389 --> 00:56:14.389
Do you remember your brother at all from when you were a kid?

00:56:18.899 --> 00:56:19.899
No.

00:56:20.899 --> 00:56:22.169
That's a huge relief.

00:56:27.239 --> 00:56:30.309
(Ms. Shin)

00:56:30.379 --> 00:56:31.539
Call me now.

00:56:36.379 --> 00:56:39.049
So, when is the surgery?

00:56:39.649 --> 00:56:41.289
Well, it's...

00:56:44.659 --> 00:56:45.959
It's the hospital. Just a moment.

00:56:47.989 --> 00:56:49.059
Yes, Doctor.

00:56:53.029 --> 00:56:54.569
What do you mean?

00:56:55.169 --> 00:56:56.369
What do you mean, it's cancelled?

00:56:59.309 --> 00:57:02.579
That's ridiculous, Doctor. How can this be happening?

00:57:05.239 --> 00:57:07.049
Yes, I understand. I'm on my way.

00:57:09.849 --> 00:57:11.919
Eun Oh, I am so sorry.

00:57:12.219 --> 00:57:15.819
The donor... They said he suddenly backed out.

00:57:16.689 --> 00:57:19.589
Let's talk on the way.

00:57:20.489 --> 00:57:22.799
No, it's okay. You should get to the hospital.

00:57:23.129 --> 00:57:25.329
No, I can't just leave you like this.

00:57:26.299 --> 00:57:28.669
Your place is on the way. I'll drop you off.

00:57:32.139 --> 00:57:33.409
(Who's the author? I hope the next one comes soon.)

00:57:33.469 --> 00:57:34.739
(Dokgo Chan's name is hilarious, but he's so cool.)

00:57:44.419 --> 00:57:45.419
Park Yeong Ra.

00:57:46.549 --> 00:57:49.459
- What? - Stop staring at it. Let's go home.

00:57:49.589 --> 00:57:51.019
Hey, it's already 6pm.

00:57:51.119 --> 00:57:54.289
Hey, over 10,000 people have read my webtoon.

00:57:54.659 --> 00:57:56.529
You've told me that three times already.

00:57:58.229 --> 00:58:01.899
Everyone's saying it's amazing. They're wondering who the author is.

00:58:02.469 --> 00:58:06.109
They're asking for the next episode, and they love Dokgo Chan.

00:58:07.139 --> 00:58:08.709
They're asking if So Ri is going to die...

00:58:08.979 --> 00:58:10.879
and if it has a sad ending.

00:58:11.739 --> 00:58:14.179
Reading the comments is so surreal and exciting.

00:58:14.349 --> 00:58:16.579
You'll never read them all even if you stay up all night.

00:58:16.579 --> 00:58:17.979
They'll just keep coming.

00:58:18.149 --> 00:58:19.949
So just read them tomorrow when you're back here.

00:58:20.049 --> 00:58:21.589
Just a little bit longer.

00:58:23.559 --> 00:58:26.189
You'd better stop before your mom gets suspicious.

00:58:30.299 --> 00:58:32.399
It's always my mom.

00:58:32.829 --> 00:58:33.929
Come on, get up.

00:58:38.439 --> 00:58:40.609
How can this happen? How could the donor disappear...

00:58:40.669 --> 00:58:43.039
when the surgery is less than ten days away?

00:58:45.109 --> 00:58:49.449
So what are we supposed to do now? There aren't any other donors.

00:58:52.589 --> 00:58:53.889
I'm on my way now.

00:58:54.519 --> 00:58:56.289
Yes, of course. I'll drive carefully.

00:59:04.699 --> 00:59:06.969
Is the situation that bad?

00:59:11.869 --> 00:59:15.239
It's been bad for a while now.

00:59:17.639 --> 00:59:19.409
I'm sorry for worrying you.

00:59:39.899 --> 00:59:41.399
You can drop me off here.

00:59:44.239 --> 00:59:46.109
Please drive safely.

00:59:52.779 --> 00:59:53.979
Why are you getting out?

00:59:56.049 --> 00:59:57.419
You're my daughter.

00:59:57.949 --> 00:59:59.819
I can't just drop you off like a passenger.

01:00:05.529 --> 01:00:06.559
And...

01:00:09.329 --> 01:00:11.059
I can call you, right?

01:00:14.129 --> 01:00:15.129
Of course.

01:00:16.569 --> 01:00:17.769
You should get going.

01:00:37.259 --> 01:00:38.319
Eun Oh.

01:00:40.629 --> 01:00:43.529
- Oh, Mom. - Who was that stylish woman?

01:00:45.129 --> 01:00:46.269
A client.

01:00:47.829 --> 01:00:50.339
The one who got you that health screening?

01:00:51.439 --> 01:00:52.439
Yes.

01:00:53.939 --> 01:00:55.709
We had a meeting today,

01:00:56.379 --> 01:00:58.409
and she dropped me off since it was on her way.

01:00:58.839 --> 01:01:00.449
Did you go grocery shopping?

01:01:00.849 --> 01:01:03.579
What? Yes, I stopped by the restaurant.

01:01:04.119 --> 01:01:06.119
The galbi has aged perfectly.

01:01:08.049 --> 01:01:09.219
Of course, it has.

01:01:11.119 --> 01:01:13.089
But you're home from work early today.

01:01:13.729 --> 01:01:14.729
Yes.

01:01:15.529 --> 01:01:17.499
Hey, about that lady...

01:01:17.729 --> 01:01:20.929
When will you actually start construction for her?

01:01:21.429 --> 01:01:24.339
You got 30,000 dollars as your design fee months ago.

01:01:26.009 --> 01:01:27.009
Well...

01:01:27.869 --> 01:01:30.679
There were some leaking issues, and some other things came up.

01:01:31.639 --> 01:01:32.649
Come on, let's go inside.

01:01:34.549 --> 01:01:35.979
She paid you months ago.

01:01:36.379 --> 01:01:38.279
I guess rich people are never in a hurry.

01:01:38.649 --> 01:01:39.689
Hey, wait up.

01:01:50.129 --> 01:01:53.269
Eun Oh, go and get washed up. Gang Oh will be home soon.

01:01:53.899 --> 01:01:55.399
- Should I? - Yes.

01:01:55.499 --> 01:01:57.469
- I'll wash up quickly, then. - Okay.

01:02:02.879 --> 01:02:04.879
(Glass noodles)

01:02:14.189 --> 01:02:15.319
Yes, this is Lee Ji Hyuk.

01:02:15.689 --> 01:02:19.489
- The chairman's ready. Come on up. - Okay.

01:02:37.379 --> 01:02:39.009
(Director Ko Seong Hui)

01:02:40.779 --> 01:02:42.519
(I'm sorry about earlier, for asking you to call me Mom.)

01:02:43.519 --> 01:02:44.649
What is this all about?

01:02:50.159 --> 01:02:52.589
I'm sorry about earlier, for asking you to call me Mom.

01:02:53.959 --> 01:02:55.059
Call her Mom?

01:02:55.859 --> 01:02:57.629
Call me that when it feels right to you.

01:02:57.929 --> 01:03:00.299
I just want to hear it once before I die.

01:03:00.599 --> 01:03:01.669
My daughter.

01:03:02.299 --> 01:03:03.369
"My daughter?"

01:03:11.439 --> 01:03:12.609
Wait. Then...

01:03:13.449 --> 01:03:15.979
That woman was...

01:03:48.009 --> 01:03:50.349
(Our Golden Days)

01:03:50.519 --> 01:03:52.949
What are you talking about? You did this without talking to me?

01:03:53.019 --> 01:03:55.089
You were going to send your father to your brother?

01:03:55.149 --> 01:03:57.719
Business is about money. This is no place for emotions.

01:03:57.819 --> 01:03:59.759
That's why he's still an amateur.

01:03:59.859 --> 01:04:03.429
This is so lame. I need a chance to at least look at her...

01:04:03.499 --> 01:04:05.159
to see if I could ever see her as more than a friend.

01:04:05.229 --> 01:04:08.429
Mom is lying. What if she's having an affair?

01:04:08.529 --> 01:04:09.739
I need to get to the bottom of this.

01:04:09.939 --> 01:04:13.809
They need a compatibility test. Eun Oh, would you consider...

01:04:13.939 --> 01:04:18.239
- No, never mind, Eun Oh. - I'll get tested.